<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,833]" box="[199,1435,152,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,421,152,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Taxonomic position</emphasis>
. The external characters of the males (very small size, the translucent wings without pattern),
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,833]" box="[151,1435,186,209]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">the male genital structure (membranous gnathos), and behaviour (daytime activity,) support the status of this species as a</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,833]" box="[151,649,220,244]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
member of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Bruand, 1853" authorityName="Bruand" authorityYear="1853" box="[382,646,220,244]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[382,491,220,244]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Stygioides</emphasis>
Bruand, 1853
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
