<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="600" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,833]" box="[199,1436,255,279]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,256,279]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reisser" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[327,571,255,279]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persephone">
<emphasis box="[327,571,255,279]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Stygioides persephone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can readily be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bruand" authorityYear="1853" box="[1039,1148,255,279]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1039,1148,255,279]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Stygioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the following
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,833]" box="[151,243,290,313]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">features:</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
- in males of 
<taxonomicName authority="colchica (Herrich-Schaffer, 1851)" authorityName="colchica (Herrich-Schaffer" authorityYear="1851" box="[376,869,324,348]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="colchica" subSpecies="colchica">
<emphasis box="[376,594,324,348]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. colchica colchica</emphasis>
(Herrich-Schäffer, 1851)
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[885,932,325,348]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">type</typeStatus>
locality 
<collectingRegion box="[1030,1116,325,348]" country="Turkey" name="Amasya" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Amasia</collectingRegion>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[1136,1347,324,348]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="colchica" subSpecies="dercetis">
<emphasis box="[1136,1347,324,348]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. colchica dercetis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Grum- Grshimailo, 1900) (
<typeStatus box="[453,500,360,383]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">type</typeStatus>
locality Valle fl. Arnon (Wadi-el-Modshib, Moabia) [Wadi al Madjib River, 
<collectingCountry box="[1314,1391,360,383]" name="Jordan" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Jordan</collectingCountry>
]), 
<taxonomicName authority="Yakovlev &amp; Saldaitis, 2011" authorityName="Yakovlev &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nupponenorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. nupponenorum</emphasis>
Yakovlev &amp; Saldaitis, 2011
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[737,784,394,417]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">type</typeStatus>
locality 
<collectingCountry box="[885,962,394,417]" name="Turkey" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[976,1070,394,417]" name="Turkey" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
, 
<quantity box="[1084,1155,394,417]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" unit="km" value="20.0">20 km</quantity>
W. 
<collectingRegion box="[1205,1294,394,417]" country="Turkey" name="Antalya" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Antalya</collectingRegion>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Staudinger, 1887)" authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Staudinger" baseAuthorityYear="1887" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aethiops">
<emphasis box="[1315,1436,393,417]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. aethiops</emphasis>
(Staudinger, 1887)
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[460,508,429,452]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">type</typeStatus>
locality Namangan; Margelan) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Grum-Grshimailo, 1893)" authorityName="Grum-Grshimailo" authorityYear="1893" baseAuthorityName="Grum-Grshimailo" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[900,1285,428,452]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="psyche">
<emphasis box="[900,1000,428,452]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. psyche</emphasis>
(Grum-Grshimailo, 1893)
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1300,1347,429,452]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">type</typeStatus>
locality desertis Kyzyl-kum dictis, ad puteum Sarbi-kuduk) the wings are semi-transparent (in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reisser" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[1175,1325,463,487]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persephone">
<emphasis box="[1175,1325,463,487]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. persephone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the wings are not transparent, densely covered with brown scales);
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,833]" box="[199,1138,532,556]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
- in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" authorityYear="1851" box="[272,389,532,556]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colchica">
<emphasis box="[272,389,532,556]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. colchica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the process on costal edge of valva is 2× larger than in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reisser" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[982,1132,532,556]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persephone">
<emphasis box="[982,1132,532,556]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. persephone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,833]" box="[199,1349,567,591]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
- in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yakovlev &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2011" box="[272,460,567,591]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nupponenorum">
<emphasis box="[272,460,567,591]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. nupponenorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the phallus is curved in median ⅓, in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reisser" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[867,1016,567,591]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persephone">
<emphasis box="[867,1016,567,591]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. persephone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is bent in the proximal third;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
- in 
<taxonomicName authority="Saldaitis &amp; Yakovlev, 2007" authorityName="Saldaitis &amp; Yakovlev" authorityYear="2007" box="[273,688,601,625]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ivinskisi">
<emphasis box="[273,387,601,625]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. ivinskisi</emphasis>
Saldaitis &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yakovlev" box="[522,688,602,625]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" refString="Yakovlev, R. V. &amp; Witt, Th. (2007) Dyspessa aphrodite sp. n. from Greece (Cossidae). Nota lepidopterologica, 30 (2), 411 - 414." type="journal article" year="2007">Yakovlev, 2007</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(type locality Lebanon W., Tanourine env.) the fore wing is wide and short; border between sclerotized (proximal) and membranous (distal) parts is indistinct; in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reisser" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[1238,1390,636,660]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persephone">
<emphasis box="[1238,1390,636,660]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. persephone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this border is distinct;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,833]" box="[199,1420,705,729]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
- in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Grum-Grshimailo" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[272,372,705,729]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="psyche">
<emphasis box="[272,372,705,729]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. psyche</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the phallus is straight and thick, in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reisser" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[751,901,705,729]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persephone">
<emphasis box="[751,901,705,729]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. persephone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is thin and strongly bent in the proximal third;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,833]" box="[199,1409,740,764]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
- in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Staudinger" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[272,389,740,764]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aethiops">
<emphasis box="[272,389,740,764]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. aethiops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the thorax and abdomen are covered with pale grey scales, in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reisser" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[1053,1203,740,764]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persephone">
<emphasis box="[1053,1203,740,764]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. persephone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with brown scales;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
- in all other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bruand" authorityYear="1853" box="[485,594,775,799]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[485,594,775,799]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Stygioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the antennae comb processes of males are 1.5–3.0 × longer than the antennae rod diameter, in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reisser" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[420,569,809,833]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Stygioides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persephone">
<emphasis box="[420,569,809,833]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">S. persephone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are shorter, equal to the antennae rod diameter.
</paragraph>
